Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_dont_use(25.10)                                        set_dont_use(25.10)

Name
       set_dont_use  -  Prevents the specified design, hierarchical module, or
       library cells from being used during optimization

Syntax
       set_dont_use

       [-help]

       <object_list>[true | false]

       Prevents the specified design, hierarchical module,  or  library  cells
       from  being  used during optimization. However, optimization is allowed
       to size out don't use cells if instances are already there in the  ini-
       tial netlist.

Parameters
       <object_list>
              Specifies the list of library cells.

       true | false
              Sets or removes the set_dont_use attribute for the specified ob-
              ject list.

              Default: true

Examples
              * The following command prevents the specified library cell from
                being used during optimization:

                set_dont_use [get_lib_cells {and2}]

Related Information
              * get_lib_cells

